 JUnit, specifically `testImplementation 'org.junit.jupiter:junit-jupiter-params:6.0.0'`, `testRuntimeOnly 'org.junit.jupiter:junit-jupiter-engine:6.0.0'`, and `testRuntimeOnly 'org.junit.platform:junit-platform-launcher:6.0.0'`. There could be conflicts with the existing `org.junit.jupiter.api.Test` from the plugin. I’m also concerned about compatibility between JUnit Vintage 5.9 and Platform 6, especially since there might be JUnit 4 dependencies involved. I need to navigate this carefully to avoid conflicts.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Investigating plugin issues**\\n\\nI'm considering that the TCK plugin might have enforced version 5.9.2 due to certain constraints. My build cache holds version 6 from a prior attempt, which raises the possibility that the generated agent attempted to add something. It's curious there wasn't a compile failure. The native SVM error indicates a version 5.9 issue instead of 6. I think inspecting the native error could reveal missing metadata from the previous setup.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_s8306cbsEVtO7c55ssEdCc13|fc_0764dc2e4879d756016a286030b9d08193801acf2f4d25b444", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.springframework/spring-test/7.0.0/build/native/nativeTestCompile/svm_err_b_20260609T204553.858_pid3904707.md", "offset": 1, "limit": 260}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 860, "output": 2975, "cacheRead": 35840, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 39675, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1781030876229, "responseId": "resp_0764dc2e4879d756016a285fdcaff8819389f70a5a4af06f88"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_s8306cbsEVtO7c55ssEdCc13|fc_0764dc2e4879d756016a286030b9d08193801acf2f4d25b444", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# GraalVM Native Image Error Report\n\n## Build Output\n\n```\n=================