[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating JUnit compatibility**\n\nI’m trying to figure out how the JUnit 6 engine might work, but it could fail due to the absence of a provider. With JUnit 4, the `@Test` runs fine with Vintage. However, Jupiter 6 might struggle with `@ClassTemplate`. On the other hand, Jupiter 5.9 doesn’t recognize `@ClassTemplate` but notices `@Testable`. It seems to identify all `@Testable` classes and resolves test methods exclusively with `@Test`, rather than JUnit 4, so it might ignore certain things. I think it should work out fine!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0764dc2e4879d756016a286073a04081939f3aa71eeb64ab63\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqKGCarXlnR4WdC9JkZml7kVIJqKtmDme3vcEfOwxuiSrc20z64aQcN38ozJQqvVQ6OQ10ht9o-HDAPMUK3YuK_Eeybw3nx-NHKtA5mSmv4KcbmH6__pjWmG6lYtij0YoiGqL28UR1Rc7rHJt9mU--EWfO6bfzqlMISq6XH7d6lcaQaiL1FYNIOmFGwD9RkWlD3-qQ27l9-HLv67hEqHVSuYwu5ZYWbu3PkFySGTxOXjnEmZYAEviVCz-fxiuGxJJKra-eD0_nt6fP-j4zN7KsTRu9jxnuEiA4gVMWMsL9gDb5oewaoDMibFejPRNEBDiINXJQNvBJoHpcol_5Sn8zMsuXPltPVnn_WVfkAmXE_BkEZgjvfsARBT63QEIvKnDjCtdo7eYawXZJDH-Ax5abGeJXoYY1xF2qDUc9-pcF4-33vBHjYhiBk443U_AD4cvNGPa9dgkImiXx8mkFXatMadGJ7PjRdDftZyJW73qBrHWE_3VXNpT12QTBV0xB7lP9aagFWi5a80TBMSYrzu5eidLQia_Q4qS7owBtSU-zTV2vaEYxRMJGmpcDjrw1XyKTBtMGiig0whyApPPO_P11Don66wHGJjDvilCh7fMGRKF1m6f4HS2uR2YRNhVgYJA5ugc-nD2oe0NYvL7Oq0084Yq1tdRYOZId05SHl0YpYbM7pMR-r0L3oJVCQD5jn0fCZnw9s2xNtis_H_1UPiaJ7bml7YfUUJ2OHmyU2SHNdcX6XJltk2jmPKglQo_LIc8DpVV77Vyl67tcIDy7mZDmMmwdOpAaxjN2pC53aaomrnFbFYoxi2o4nKCfCa_-LO0ti72QRFmgc-fI-dYmszbxi6jYexKQpBZLWZDa_ImfXzxyFtInIhxVZ1A-j5FKPSTKMBPRkNVLiNSPIUq44p8hBU-ieRh4RpgYYnzw2YnfDlY07CD0Uz_nCJz1IDkJSSNFjSZ30U7NIpDxp2RHK2TZBkvbhmAWjt2x_p-Sy6VdLekNvD-VzDUQ6id3k1p0XcUJ9S-tfJnlnVGf30LL9rDjwKo3-EPRzh0epThtLUM6JJTzW8SfAXNOTUo_UBeJOLIQNxTMnJ065kSCXiKfNgtrvW7M2b79yA47KG4rryBYlLfrz8a558aAKrH-xBq7liU7411K_bkMteg9zwZNxyxJzceOOXh0Crj0Ej0Tq_QO3JwBlo7