[thinking] **Considering JUnit updates**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm thinking about future updates to the JUnit 6 engine. If the internal scanner's Launcher starts using Jupiter 6, there could be issues with classpath scanning, leading to discovery errors if there’s no class template provider. This might cause our tests to fail, which is concerning! I'm also wondering if we should consider a version-agnostic approach. Maybe once Spring 7 comes out, it will eventually support the TCK for JUnit 6.
[thinking] 
